**Proposed minimum-change fix** — add `checkUsername` right after `baseUrl` in `lib/services/api_service.dart`:

```dart
  static Future<bool> checkUsername(String username) async {
    try {
      final response = await http.get(
        Uri.parse('$baseUrl/api/check-username?username=${Uri.encodeQueryComponent(username)}'),
      );
      if (response.statusCode == 200) {
        final data = jsonDecode(response.body);
        return data['available'] == true;
      }
      return false;
    } catch (_) {
      return false;
    }
  }
```

Matches the backend's `/api/check-username` contract (returns `{"available": bool}`). On any error/network failure it returns `false` (keeps the Sign Up button disabled rather than letting someone through), which is what the caller already expects.

OK to add it?

Clean. On `V17`, no uncommitted changes. Safe to edit.

